e announcer, and he continued to grow and impress in his role at CBS Sports and he was eventually promoted and became a member of the CBS Sports Network show announce crew in 2018.<ref>https://www.viacomcbspressexpress.com/cbs-sports/shows/golf-on-cbs/bios?id=mark-immelman</ref>\n \nMark is also an analyst on the CBS Sports digital podcast \u201cThe First Cut\u201d and a golf analyst for CBS Sports HQ.<ref>https://www.cbssports.com/podcasts/the-first-cut-golf-podcast/</ref>\n \nIn his combined radio and television career, Mark has broadcasted two of the four [[Men's major golf championships|Majors]] in professional golf ([[Masters Tournament|The Masters]] and [[PGA Championship|the PGA Championship]]).  He has also been an announcer at a number of [[World Golf Championships]] (WGC) events.  He has also announced and called three [[Presidents Cup|Presidents Cups]].\n\n==Awards==\n2009 [[NCAA Division II]] Coach of the Year <ref>http://www.csucougars.com/mobile/staff.aspx?staff=35</ref><br>\n2017 Columbus State Athletics [[List of halls and walks of fame|Hall of Fame]] inductee <ref>http://csucougars.com/news/2017/3/16/general-2017-csu-hall-of-fame-class-announced.aspx</ref>\n\n==Personal Life==\nImmelman lives with his wife, Tracy, and two daughters in [[Columbus, Georgia|Columbus]], [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]].\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n==External links==\n*[http://markimmelman.com/ Mark Immelman official website]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Immelman, Mark}}\n[[Category:1970 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:College golf coaches in the United States]]\n[[Category:College golfers in the United States]]\n[[Category:Columbus State Cougars athletes]]\n[[Category:Golf writers and broadcasters]]\n[[Category:People from Somerset West]]\n[[Category:South African emigrants to the United States]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Cape Town]]\n", "name_user": "Bazinwanga", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/