15-05-05. \u0420\u0435\u043f\u0435\u0442\u0438\u0446\u0438\u044f \u043f\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0434\u0430 \u041f\u043e\u0431\u0435\u0434\u044b 086.jpg|170px]]\n| Armoured Personnel Carrier\n| {{Flagu|Soviet Union}} \n| 18<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deagel.com/equipment/Wheeled-Armored-Fighting-Vehicles/BTR-70.htm|title=BTR-70 Report between 1992 and 2012|website=Deagel.com|access-date=26 April 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140427011039/http://www.deagel.com/equipment/Wheeled-Armored-Fighting-Vehicles/BTR-70.htm|archive-date=27 April 2014|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n| \n|-\n| [[BTR-60]]\n| [[File:BTR-60PB NVA.JPG|170px]]\n| Armoured Personnel Carrier\n| {{Flagu|Soviet Union}} \n| 6<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tanknutdave.com/the-russian-btr-8x8-series/|title=The Russian BTR-60PB 8\u00d78 Wheeled Armoured Personnel Carrier - TankNutDave|work=TankNutDave|accessdate=15 February 2015}}</ref>\n| \n|-\n| [[Alvis Saracen|Saracen]]\n| [[File:Saracen-latrun-2.jpg|170px]]\n| Armoured Personnel Carrier\n| {{Flagu|United Kingdom}}\n| 10<ref name=\"ZA\"/>\n| 20 delivered.<ref name=trade/>\n|-\n| [[Saxon (vehicle)|Saxon]]\n| [[File:Saxon Recovery Version.jpg|170px]]\n| Armoured Personnel Carrier\n| {{Flagu|United Kingdom}}\n| 75<ref name=trade/>\n| Serviceability doubtful.<ref name=\"ZA\"/>\n|-\n| [[Panhard M3]]\n| [[File:PanhardM3.png|170px]]\n| Armoured Personnel Carrier\n| {{Flagu|France}}\n| 18<ref name=\"ZA\"/>\n|-\n| [[Ezugwu]]\n| [[]]\n| Armoured Personnel Carrier\n| {{Flagu|Nigeria}}\n| 10\n| Total of 28 ordered<ref>https://www.defenceweb.co.za/land/land-land/nigerian-army-orders-locally-made-ezugwu-armoured-vehicles/</ref>\n|-\n! style=\"align: center; background: lavender;\" colspan=\"7\" | '''[[Infantry mobility vehicle]]s'''\n|-\n| [[Igirigi APC|Igirigi]]\n|\n| MRAP\n| {{Flagu|Nigeria}}\n| \n| Replaced the ''Pf1''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.defenceweb.co.za/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=26569:nigeria-opens-ballistic-armour-facto