ian Defense Review\">{{cite web|url=http://issuu.com/ukrainian_defense_review/docs/udr-04-2014/15|title=KRAZ Trucks on Military Service|author=Ukrainian Defense Review|website=Issuu.com|accessdate=4 May 2015}}</ref>\n| [[File:Iraqi KrAZ trucks.jpg|170px]]\n| Utility Truck\n| {{Flagu|Ukraine}}\n| 40<ref>https://www.defenceweb.co.za/land/land-land/ukraines-autokraz-partners-with-nigerias-proforce/</ref>\n| Some locally manufactured.<ref>https://www.defenceweb.co.za/land/land-land/ukraines-autokraz-partners-with-nigerias-proforce/</ref>\n|}\n\n===Engineering Vehicles===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! style=\"text-align: left;\"|Name\n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Photo\n! style=\"text-align: left;\"|Type\n! style=\"text-align: left;\"|Country of Origin\n! style=\"text-align: left;\"|In Service\n! style=\"text-align: left;\"|Notes\n|-\n| [[BOZENA 5]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.naij.com/1077090-nigerian-army-acquires-sophisticated-military-equipment-fight-boko-haram-pho.html|title=Nigerian army acquires more sophisticated equipment to fight Boko Haram (photos)|date=10 December 2016|website=Naij.com}}</ref>\n|\n| Unmanned ground vehicle\n| {{flagu|Slovakia}}\n|\n| clearance of all conventional antipersonnel and antitank land mines and for IED removal assistance.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bozena.eu/general-b5/|title=BOZENA 5 - medium demining system - Bo\u017eena|website=Bozena.eu}}</ref>\n|-\n|Vickers AVLB<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite book|title=Jane's Armour and Artillery 2003\u20132004}}</ref>\n|\n|Armored Bridge-layer\n|United Kingdom\n|26 (status unknown)\n|\n|-\n|Vickers ARV<ref name=\":1\" />\n|\n|Armored Recovery Vehicle\n|United Kingdom\n|12 (Status unknown)\n|\n|}\n\n===Utility Vehicle===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! style=\"text-align: left;\"|Name\n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Photo\n! style=\"text-align: left;\"|Type\n! style=\"text-align: left;\"|Country of Origin\n! style=\"text-align: left;\"|In Service\n! style=\"text-align: left;\"|Notes\n|-\n| [[Pinzgauer High-Mobility All-Terrain Vehicle|Pinzgauer]]<ref name=\"Haflinger\">{{cite web|url=http://tdc.haflinger-4wd.com/countries/nigeria.php|title=Steyr Puch Haflinger TDC - Nigeria|author=Constantin Kiesling|website=Tdc.haflinger-4wd.com|accessdate=15 February 2015}}</ref>\n| [[File:Pinzgauer 710-IMG 4935-40.jpg|170px]]\n| High-Mobility All-Terrain Vehicle\n| {{Flagu|Austria}}\n|\n| \n|-\n| [[Land Rover]]\n| [[File:Lrwolf2.jpg|170px]]\n| Utility Vehicle\n| {{Flagu|United Kingdom}} {{Flagu|Nigeria}}\n|\n| Some of local manufacture.<ref name=\"Bassey\"/>\n|-\n| [[Haflinger (vehicle)|Haflinger]]\n| [[File:Haflinger1967.jpg|170px]]\n| Utility Vehicle\n| {{Flagu|Austria}}\n| 400<ref name=\"Haflinger\"/>\n| \n|-\n| [[Toyota Hilux]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ekitistate.gov.ng/2012/02/fayemi-donates-2-hilux-pick-up-to-the-army/|title=The Official Website of the Government of Ekiti State, Nigeria \u00bb Fayemi donates 2 Hilux pick-up to the Army|work=The Official Website of the Government of Ekiti State, Nigeria|accessdate=15 February 2015}}</ref>\n| [[File:Toyota Hilux 2009 2.5 D-4D.jpg|170px]]\n| Light Truck\n| {{Flagu|Japan}}\n| \n| \n|-\n| [[Tarpan Honker]]<ref>{{cite tweet|user=RemigiuszWilk|author=Remigiusz Wilk|number=773941918422228992|date=8 September 2016|title=25 Honker\u00f3w w SZ Nigerii: 3 testowe, 10 Scorpion 4x4 NAF i 12 20-os. transportowe 6x4 (176 KM i 2x55 l zbiornik). Zadowoleni, chc\u0105 wi\u0119cej.}}</ref><ref>{{cite tweet|user=RemigiuszWilk|author=Remigiusz Wilk|number=774549277171445760|date=10 September 2016|title=Ko\u0144cz\u0105c temat eksportowych Honker\u00f3w - dostarczone Skorpiony w u\u017cyciu przez jednostki ochrony lotniska @NigAirForce}}</ref>\n| [[File:Ko\u0142obrzeg - Honker regulacja ruchu.jpg|170px]]\n| Multipurpose Jeep\n| {{flagu|Poland}}\n| 25\n|\n|-\n| [[IVM G-12]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.defenceweb.co.za/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=46311:nigerian-army-operating-locally-made-ivm-g-12-special-purpose-vehicles&catid=50:Land&