le Rifle \n| {{Flagu|Belgium}} {{Flagu|Nigeria}}\n| Local variant designated ''NR1''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.smallarmssurvey.org/files/portal/issueareas/producers/Producers_pdf/2007_Production.pdf|title=Licensed and unlicensed production of FN Herstal products, to August 2006|publisher=Small Arms Survey|accessdate=2010-04-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100705100331/http://www.smallarmssurvey.org/files/portal/issueareas/producers/Producers_pdf/2007_Production.pdf|archive-date=5 July 2010|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.country-data.com/cgi-bin/query/r-9464.html|title=Nigeria - Arms Procurement and Defense Industries|accessdate=2010-04-10|date=June 1991}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fides.org/eng/news/2004/0407/24_2910.html|title=DOSSIER - The Question of Arms in Africa|accessdate=2010-04-10|publisher=Agenzia Fides|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090318112305/http://www.fides.org/eng/news/2004/0407/24_2910.html|archive-date=18 March 2009|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> \n|-\n| [[Heckler & Koch G3]]\n| [[File:DCB Shooting G3 pictures.jpg|150px]]\n| Battle Rifle \n| {{Flagu|West Germany}} {{Flagu|Nigeria}}\n| Some of Nigerian manufacture.<ref>[http://www.country-data.com/cgi-bin/query/r-9464.html Nigeria: Arms Procurement and Defense Industries.] Retrieved on 5 October 2008.</ref>\n|-\n| [[Beretta BM59|BM-59]]\n| [[File:Bm59.jpg|150px]]\n| Battle Rifle \n| {{Flagu|Italy}} {{Flagu|Nigeria}}\n| Some of Nigerian manufacture.<ref>[http://www.guardiannewsngr.com/editorial_opinion/article02/indexn2_html?pdate=100308&ptitle=German German small arms: The Nigerian connection.] Retrieved on 5 October 2008.</ref> \n|-\n| [[Vz. 52 rifle]]\n| [[File:Vz.52.jpg|150px]]\n| Semi-automatic rifle\n| {{Flagu|Czechoslovakia}} \n| \n|-\n! style=\"align: center; background: lavender;\" colspan=\"7\" | '''[[Machine gun]]s'''\n|-\n| [[RPK]]\n| [[File:RPK Machine Gun 7.62 x 39.jpg|150px]]\n| Light machine gun \n| {{Flagu|